11. (Is Valid and Finite) Explain how you can determine if a number is valid and finite.
The best way to perform this is using the isFinite function.

Example:
isFinite(+"5"); // converts to Number, then outputs true
isFinite(+"abc"); // converts to NaN, then outputs false
isFinite(5/0); // evaluates as Infinity, then outputs false
isFinite(-5/0); // evaluates as -Infinity, then outputs false
